  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Inspect brake switch"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not connect the coupler with the brake switch removed. The engine will recognize that the brake is depressed, and the engine will start with a single press of the ENGINE START STOP button, which is dangerous due to engine starting when not intended."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Brake switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "984_3.0_jpn_11337358_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "984_3.0_jpn_11037139_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Inspect the continuity between terminals in each position of the coupler (B) and confirm that there is continuity only between ○ and ○. If there is no continuity, Adjust the brake switch and If there is no continuity again, check again. If there is no continuity again, Replace the brake switch. Connect the coupler.",
